                            angular basic-commands



            1. to create a project : ng new project-name
            2. to run a project : ng serve --open
            3. to create a component : ng g c component-name
            4. to create a service- ng g s service_name

                            angular building blocks

            1.module : to import liabraries/root module- appmodule
            2.component:-{html,css,ts}-root component -appcomponent

                             
                             3.data binding
            
            sharing data within a component
                
                3.1 ONE WAY BINDING
                 3.1.1 component to view

                 a. string interpolation-syntax:  {{expression}}
                 b. property binding-syntax: [target-property]="sourse-property"
                         

                 3.1.2view to component
                
                 a. event binding-syntax: (event-name)="function call"
                 b. template referencing variable -syntax: #variablename 
                                act as getElementbyid



                                (change)="acnoChange($event)"
                                (change)="pswdChange($event)"


                3.2 TWO WAY BINDING  

                    data flow in two directions -import formsModule in AppModule-
                    syntax:[(ngModel)]="variablename"
                     
                    set  name property of the tag if we used ngModel inside a form tag
                    
  

          4. App routing module- To set path for an html page
         
          5. Dependency Injection- to communicate data between class/component
         
          6. Angular services - to keep redundant code
    
          7. ngSubmit - to submit an entire form

          8. angular directives: to manipulate DOM
             8.1 component directives
             8.2 structural directives(cirtain condition based...add , remove tag)
                 8.2.1 ngIf -syntax- *ngIf="condition"
                 8.2.2 ngSwitch
                 8.2.3 ngFor
             8.3 Attribute directives- to apply set of style to html
                 8.3.1   in build- ngClass 
                 8.3.2   user defined-   
          9. angular forms
              9.1 template driven angular form -first design the html page
              9.2 model driven angular forms - first design the model in ts file
                 9.2.1 Reactive forms- add validation to the forms-ReactiveFormsModule
                       {form group-form builder class,form array,form control name}








